OL,6,FThe defendants had made thousands of
OL,7,Ffalse claims for benefits using real
OL,8,Fpeople or hijacked identities, with
OL,9,Fclaims supported by an array of forged
OL,10,Fdocuments including tenancy
OL,11,Fagreements, payslips and letters from
OL,12,Flandlords, employers, schools and GPs.
OL,14,FIf claims were rejected, the
OL,15,Ffraudsters would try time and again
OL,16,Funtil they were granted.
